Prosper Loan Interest Rate Factors¶

by Roy Amante A. Salvador¶

Investigation Overview¶

Prosper is a peer to peer lending platform for US residents. In this investigation, we are interested on finding out the factors in predicting a loan's interest rate at Prosper. Interest rate is a metric for determining how hard it is to borrow money.

Dataset Overview¶

The data consists of 113,387 Prosper Loan Listings with 81 variables such as amount of loan, interest rate, status of loan, borrower information among many more.

Distribution of Prosper Loan Interest Rates¶

  • Most common interest rates in Prosper loans fall around 15% and 30%. It's rare to have interest rates below 5% or above 35%.

Motivation: Investors and Loan Status¶

  • We like to have good interest rates with our loans to attract more investors. Interest Rate is seen to have a moderate negative correlation with the number of investors.
  • To increase our chances of successful repayment, we desire lower interest rates. Delinquent loans (Defaulted, Chargedoff and with past due) have interest rates typically more than 20%. Lower interest rates are seen for loans with healthy status.

Factor: Loan Amount and Term¶

  • Bigger loan amounts tend to have lower interest rates.
  • Loan terms with higher number of months tend to have higher interest rates.

Factor: Loan Risk Rating¶

  • Loans with high risk ratings tend to have higher interest rates. This remained consistent even after the risk rating system changed in 2009.

Factor: Loan Category and Borrower's Income Range¶

  • Purpose of the loan is also a factor. Loans for Cosmetic Procedure and Household Expenses have the highest interest rates while for Boat and Personal Loan have the lowest.
  • The higher the borrower's income is, the lower the interest rate is on their loan. Unemployed borrowers tend to have the highest interest rates at more than 25%.

Factor: Borrower's Credit Score and Group Membership¶

  • Lower interest rates are associated with loan listings whose borrowers have better Credit Score
  • Interaction with Credit Score reveals members of a group in Prosper get lower interest rates than those with no membership
  • Historically, Group membership however has always been slower in originating the loan. This might be caused by some additional process the loan listing has to go through such as group leader approval.

Factor: Timing¶

  • From 2007 to 2011, interest rates are increasing. 2011 until 2014, it became decreasing . This might be caused by economic trends (e.g. 2008 Global Financial Crisis) so timing also matters.
